    <item>
      <title>Possible class Changes? More Group Usefulness</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;message.id=9535#M9535</link>
      <description>I have been playing a druid for about 4-5 years now. I probably solo'd through the 50's and such and up to 65 in PoStorms. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
After level 66 druids like me had to start grouping again to get any amount of decent experience (after the charm nerf). &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I find grouping to be the most challanging thing for a druid right now.&#xD;
In groups they are just not as desired as other classes on either side&#xD;
of the spectrum. I get into most groups because i walk into zones and&#xD;
start asking people if they have any room. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I don't get asked to join groups.... why?&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
The reason and the solution to this problem are fairly complicated and&#xD;
I do not believe that the proposed "modes" will be of any use to me. In&#xD;
a group tides can change very quickly. Most of the time in an exp group&#xD;
where mobs are hitting in the 1500-2k range (and beyond), my job as a&#xD;
druid is to dps (if you call it that) and to spot heal if someone other&#xD;
than the tank gets aggro.&amp;nbsp; The proposed changes would make my spot heal&#xD;
rather useless and my nukes only slightly better.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
If im the groups main healer, all I am is a very very weak cleric with&#xD;
a 5k "big heal" that never crits (at least ive never seen it crit with&#xD;
max healing aa's). You all say that druids can be group healer and do&#xD;
fantastic dps (an exaggeration) at the same time. This is simply&#xD;
untrue...&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
With most tanks being in the 14k-17k (most single group situations) our&#xD;
meager 5k heal (5.7ish with aa's) needs to be casted almost constantly&#xD;
just to keep up... which gives druids at a HUGE mana deficiency. I&#xD;
believe the problem here is that while druids are semi-good at&#xD;
everything... they dont have the mana pools or regen to fill out their&#xD;
shorts (or bra's for you females).&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
When I ask myself what a druid is good for in a group, only one word&#xD;
comes to mind... Safety. We are a safety net class, we deal a little&#xD;
dps here, nuke a bit here... and evac when we have to. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
On my server (bertox) I see more druids lfg than any other class. This&#xD;
only fuels my argument above.... Druids are just not really desireable&#xD;
in groups. We need something extra... i would like to see this extra&#xD;
thing go towards our dps, our mana regen abilities, or the mana cost of&#xD;
our spells.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Throughout the levels, mana regen has always been a problem.... now as&#xD;
a more mature character with 12 mana regen coming from items and&#xD;
another 12 coming from self spells (oak and mask) the problem still&#xD;
exists. We are the only class (besides clerics) in a groupable&#xD;
situation that does not have some strong form of alternate mana&#xD;
regeneration.... we regen like hybrids, and still dont have as much&#xD;
usefulness for one thing or another. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I say to fix the druid problem, we need, less casting time and mana&#xD;
cost on our heals, a greater big heal with a chance to crit just like&#xD;
any other heal, and less mana cost and lower resist rate on our nuke&#xD;
and dot spells. Also some aa's that would increase our burst dps&#xD;
further, or maybe a spell line of pets. We are guardians of nature, we&#xD;
should be able to summon forth nature at our will in some form. These&#xD;
changes in one form or another would greatly improve a druids chance of&#xD;
being asked to join a group.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Guday Mate&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
70th assling druid&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Bertox&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
