    <item>
      <title>How I would like to see stances implemented</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;message.id=9394#M9394</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I like to both heal and DPS as my druid.  As such, I feel I have a vested interest in how druids are tweaked since any benefits/detriments to either side will affect my gameplay.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;SOE acknowledges that we have shortcomings on both the healing and DPS sides.  Their idea of stances was a way to prevent overpowering the class.  However, the problems I see on each side are not the same.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;When I am a healer, my main problem isn't the size of my heals, it's my efficiency.  When I get a good roll, chlorotrope hits for 4500hps or a 9k crit.  I don't have my ancient spells but i do have my healing aa's maxxed and a 35% healing item.  However, spam heals are very draining on my mana pool (9k buffed).  This is especially a problem when someone other than that MT takes dmg and I need to hit them with a &amp;quot;quick&amp;quot; heal.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When I'm a DPS'er, my main problem isn't mana, it's the size of my nukes.  It isn't uncommon for me to be spam nuking on a mob and be able to keep up.  Therefore, an increase in efficiency wouldn't be as helpful to me as an increase in the size of my nukes and dots.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What I would like to see is two different stances.  Instead of being mirror images of one another, they would be tailored a bit to each side of the problem.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;In &amp;quot;healer&amp;quot; mode, I'd like to see a 15% mana savings to all heal spells (spam heal, ICH, reptile and the new group heal).  In keeping with SOE's initial model of the detriment being twice as big as the benefit, I would envision this stance causing my nukes to cost 30% more mana.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In &amp;quot;DPS&amp;quot; mode, I'd like to see the proposed 25% increase to damage spells (nukes and dots).  The proposed 50% detriment to healing would be in effect.  Yes, this is a big price to pay, but with the proposed 5 minute lockouts I don't think this will be a really big problem.  Besides, there's always exodus /grin&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The DPS mode doesn't need examples, since this is the same thing we've been discussing for over a year.  Let me give you some examples on the healing mode.  I'm not counting AA's or gear in any of this since they apply all around and are therefore irrelevent percentage-wise.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Druid 68 heal - No Stance  2810 hps for 691 mana ---- 4.06 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Druid 64 ICH - No Stance 4680 hps for 600 mana ---- 7.8 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Druid 68 heal - Healing stance 2810 hps for 587 mana ---- 4.78 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Druid 64 ICH - Healing stance 4680 hps for 510 mana ---- 9.17 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For comparison, let's examine some cleric heals so we can get a feel for whether these figures are overpowered&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cleric 68 heal - 3770 hps for 740 mana ---- 5.09 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cleric 67 HoT - 1170 hps/tick for 5 ticks for 890 mana ---- 6.57 hp/m  (i believe the extra tick is inherent, correct me if i'm wrong)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cleric 70 jumbo heal - 4935 hps for 1375 mana ---- 3.59 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cleric CH - 7500 hps for 400 mana ---- 18.75 hp/m&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Our ICH is obviously not a problem since clerics would be far and away the best at that.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We approach the efficiency of a cleric with our &amp;quot;normal&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;spam&amp;quot; heal.  We would be up to 94% efficiency.  However, please note that clerics are healing for 1k more (the gap gets larger as healing focus and AA's come into play).  We would still have a lower hps per minute ratio than clerics would.  Clerics also have more healing tools (rightfully so) which allows them greater flexibility and an easier time healing. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;On the nuking side...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Our 69 nuke (fire) would do 2201 pts of dmg for 642 mana.  3.43 dmg/mana ratio&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Our 70 nuke (cold) would do 1892 pts of dmg for 495 mana.  3.82 dmg/mana ratio&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cleric's 69 chromatic nuke does 1200 pts of dmg for 375 mana.  3.2 dmg/mana ratio&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cleric's 67 nuke 1424 pts of damage for 430 mana.  3.31 dmg/mana&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Their chromatic nuke would be 94% as efficient as our fire nuke (slightly higher since we tend to debuff and that costs a bit).  Their non-chromatic would be 86% as efficient as our more efficient cold nuke. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;While we would approach clerics in healing efficiency, their heals would be bigger.  Likewise, while in healing mode, their nukes would approach ours in efficiency but our nukes would be bigger (I'll admit that the size of bigger nukes/heals has a discrepancy).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
