      <title>Druid AA swarm pet</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;message.id=9371#M9371</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;Been meaning to bring this up for awhile.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In DodH most of the classes, including the druid, go a swarm pet to be I think equivalent to the awesome shammy one that was given in I think OOWAR expansion.  For most classes, this included a 3/5/7ish pets depending on which level of aa the class was at (or 3/4/5).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Here is my issue.  We  were given a pet too, woot. the problem is where other get multiple pets we get one that stays around for a longer period of time as you proceed into the higher levles.  it hits for a max of 350, not bad, but hits very slow, and dies if hit by anything harder then a light wind.  The largest disadvantage I see, is that is the other classes pets are hit, they at least have the rest of them to keep dpsing.  if our pet is hit, he dies period, the end of the aa for the next 25 or so minutes.  Also, sometimes he just quits attacking or if the one mob you send him after dies he will sit around and watch the rest of the battle.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;While I would prefer ot have multiples like the other classes,  this pet would be ok if he would survive some hits (viritually impossible to get a qh off on him).  I can live with one pet mind you, but please give him some defense and hitpoints then so he can survive long enough to do dps in any but the most perfect situations.  While it may seem logical to say well we give him more hps, maybe even as much as the total of the other pets.  issue is that  3x almost nothing is stil nothing so he gets one rounded anyway.  At least with multiple pets, the mob has to change targets each kill.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;  Also have done parses on mine vs others and find our seems to do substantially less.   average af about 1100 damage during his life with a max of about 1800 if he hits every time at level one (swings once it appears about every tick, but misses quite often).  I have level two and he seldom seems to get a double attack, not sure.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;DPS over 30 seconds for 1100 damage is 36ish plus or minus.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;DPS of bard pet i need to get the stats on but I believe guildie said it was more then double that, and that was assuming survivale of our pet.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Not sure if others have the same issue in ae's, I hope they do, but of course, do not bother using pet during for an ae mob, unless that gets changed.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Just another minor, but easy to address item to consider for the issues list.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
