      <title>Current Stance Poll/Discussion - 3/23/06</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;message.id=9367#M9367</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Ok yall, it's been hacked and slashed to death, but seriously, we need to come up with a unified voice as to where we would like to see our class heading.  Considering Stances have been on the idea-board for over a year, and we cannot expect to see any changes for a long time.  (Remember, they've stated they had to do Shammy reinvisioning/fixes and see'ing where that takes them, before they mess with druids.)  This is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; the thread to discuss how it sucks they haven't been put in yet, the Dev's making announcements and not backign them up, how druids have &amp;quot;cleric-envy&amp;quot;, how druid's want everything and don't want to give up anything, or any other junk that brings the discussion off topic or otherwise derailed.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The purpose is to decide if we even WANT the purposed Stance changes&lt;/strong&gt;.  It is my belief that after discussing and thinkiing about the potential changes stances would do for us, the majority of us feel that Stances WILL NOT do what they were originally thought of for: To help druids close the Effect/Efficiency gap in healing so as to make Clerics, Druids, and Shammy, and by doing this, increase the desireability of druids.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please state if you would like to see Stances eventually implimented in the current proposed state (+25% increase, -50% decrease), and if you would like, your reasons why.  I would like to focus this specifically on if the druid community wants this or to ditch this idea, and find an alternative solution.  I would rather wait on alternatives and do that in a seperate thread if the results of this say druids don't want them.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
